overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, providing a detailed specification to ensure all acceptance
  criteria were met. The agent meticulously analyzed the existing codebase
  against the requirements, identifying critical gaps such as the absence of a
  tiredness severity scale, COMISA detection, insufficient sleep syndrome logic,
  external resource links in reports, and weighted scoring for Excessive Daytime
  Sleepiness (EDS). Following this assessment, the agent systematically
  implemented each missing feature. This involved updating data types,
  validation schemas, UI components for input, and the complex logic for
  generating personalized reports in both web and PDF formats. The enhancements
  significantly improved the diagnostic capabilities and resource provision of
  the questionnaire, bringing it into closer alignment with the user's detailed
  specifications.
